{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0844\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0844\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0844\"\nms.assetid: ccf74e01-292a-42d0-897c-8add7aee2118\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0844\nCannot use local variable 'name' before it is declared. The declaration of the local variable hides the field 'name'.  \n  \n An identifier can have only one meaning in a given block. Local variables that have the same name as class fields can hide the field by introducing a second meaning for the identifier. Therefore the compiler generates an error when you refer to a class field in a method, and then declare a local variable by the same name.  \n  \n## To correct this error  \n  \n-   Use `this.num` to refer to the class field.  \n  \n-   Give the local variable a different name from the class field.  \n  \n## Example  \n The following code generates CS0844:  \n  \n```csharp  \nclass Test  \n    {  \n        int num;  \n        public void TestMethod()  \n        {  \n            num = 5; // CS0844  \n            int num = 6;        }  \n        public static int Main()  \n        {  \n            return 1;  \n        }  \n    }  \n```\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0844\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0844\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0844\"\nms.assetid: ccf74e01-292a-42d0-897c-8add7aee2118","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0844","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0844","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0844","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[172,193],"content":"Compiler Error CS0844","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0844","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0844","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Cannot use local variable 'name' before it is declared.","pos":[194,249]},{"content":"The declaration of the local variable hides the field 'name'.","pos":[250,311]},{"content":"An identifier can have only one me